lasscode="128" cfi:normcite="LNBNEWS LNB NEWS 18/06/2024 49" spanid="I3VH2KC3GB800000310002">LNB News 18/06/2024 49</lnci:span></lnci:content></lnci:cite></ref:cite4thisresource></ref:citations></abstract:head><abstract:body><abstract:target><casedigest:caseinfo><caseinfo:casename><caseinfo:fullcasename>Judgment Alert: Yieldpoint Stable Value Fund, LP v Kimura Commodity Trade Finance Fund Ltd [2024] EWCA Civ 639</caseinfo:fullcasename></caseinfo:casename><decision:dates><decision:decisiondate day="18" month="06" year="2024" normdate="2024-06-18"><date-text>18 June 2024</date-text></decision:decisiondate></decision:dates><jurisinfo:courtinfo><jurisinfo:courtname>Court of Appeal Civil Division</jurisinfo:courtname><jurisinfo:courtname normshortname="CACivD" /><jurisinfo:jurisdiction><jurisinfo:system>EnglandandWales</jurisinfo:system></jurisinfo:jurisdiction></jurisinfo:courtinfo></casedigest:caseinfo></abstract:target><abstract><bodytext><pgrp><p><text>Mini summary: CONTRACT ~ TERMS ~ LOAN FACILITY. The Court of Appeal, Civil Division, allowed the appeal of the appellant from a decision of the High Court, which had held that judgment was to be entered for the respondent against the appellant in the principal sum of US$5m, with interest to be determined. The parties (appellant and respondent) entered into a Master Participation Agreement for Trade Transactions (MPA). Pursuant to the MPA, the respondent fund agreed to pay US$5m to the appellant to participate in the appellant's 50% share of an existing loan facility (facility) extended to a mining company (MTV). The terms of the MPA anticipated and were intended to govern agreements under which the respondent would be a sub-participant in the appellant's trade-finance transactions (participated transactions) by way of pari passu participation as an economic stakeholder or co-venturer to the extent of its participation.  MTV defaulted on its obligations under the facility. The respondent commenced the proceedings claiming repayment of the principal sum of US$5m together with what it claimed to be unpaid interest and monthly price participations. The Court of Appeal disagreed with the High Court and held that the MTV participation was a conventional sub-participation. As MTV had defaulted prior to the Maturity Date, the respondent was not entitled to be repaid its US$5m investment.</text></p></pgrp></bodytext></abstract><section sectiontype="Summary" alternatetoccaption="Summary"><bodytext><p><text>The judgment for this case has been published.</text></p><p><text><emph typestyle="it">Yieldpoint Stable Value Fund, LP v Kimura Commodity Trade Finance Fund Ltd</emph> <lnci:cite status="valid"><lnci:case><lnci:caseref><lnci:reporter value="EWCACIV" /><lnci:edition><lnci:date year="2024" /></lnci:edition><lnci:page num="639" /></lnci:caseref></lnci:case><lnci:content><lnci:span CITE-REF="#600003#11#2024#000639#" alttext="Court of Appeal, Civil Division (England &amp; Wales)" cfi:contentclasscode="91" cfi:normcite="[2024] EWCA Civ 639" spanid="I3VH2KC3GB800000310001">[2024] EWCA Civ 639</lnci:span></lnci:content></lnci:cite></text></p></bodytext></section></abstract:body><doc:metadata><pubinfo:pubinfo><pubinfo:dates><pubinfo:pubdate day="18" month="06" year="2024"><date-text>18 June 2024</date-text></pubinfo:pubdate></pubinfo:dates><classify:classification classscheme="gsd:publicationtype"><classify:classitem><classify:classitem-identifier><classify:classname>Legal News</classify:classname></classify:classitem-identifier></classify:classitem></classify:classification></pubinfo:pubinfo><doc:docinfo doc-content-country="GB"><dc:metadata><dc:identifier lnmeta:applicability="allVersions" lnmeta:identifier-scheme="LNI">6C8X-4D43-RS9F-X4G2-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:identifier lnmeta:identifier-scheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:6C8X-4D43-RS9F-X4G2-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:date lnmeta:datetype="conversion-date">2024-06-19</dc:date><dc:title>Judgment Alert: Yieldpoint Stable Value Fund, LP v Ki